<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD50FF9E9EDFFF59DAC0D93B" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" type="key">
<keyStep id="07262E76BD50FF9E9EDFFF59DAC1DB6D" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFF59DAC1DB2B" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFF59DAC1DB2B" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
1. Mesopleuron granulose-punctate (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD50FF9E9C66FF59DD26DAD6" box="[558,635,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Charops mauroknemus sp. nov., holotype, female. A, wing; B, mesopleuron and metapleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531144/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); scutellum convex; scape and pedicel black (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD50FF9E9A08FF59DBD0DAD6" box="[1088,1165,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Charops mauroknemus sp. nov., holotype, female. A, wing; B, mesopleuron and metapleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531144/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); mandible black (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD50FF9E9B0CFF59DACCDAD6" box="[1348,1425,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Charops mauroknemus sp. nov., holotype, female. A, wing; B, mesopleuron and metapleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531144/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); palpi brown (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD50FF9E9F2AFF7CDEF0DB34" box="[354,429,249,272]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[157,1429,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Charops mauroknemus sp. nov., holotype, female. A, wing; B, mesopleuron and metapleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531144/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); hind leg entirely black (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD50FF9E9CEBFF7CDD81DB34" box="[675,732,249,272]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[224,1364,1049,1963]" captionTargetId="figure-243@6.[224,1364,1049,1963]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Charops mauroknemus sp. nov., holotype, female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531142/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).................................... 
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD7FF7CDAC1DB2B" bold="true" box="[1183,1436,249,271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9AD7FF7CDA17DB2B" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1183,1354,249,271]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroknemus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD7FF7CDA17DB2B" bold="true" box="[1183,1354,249,271]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. mauroknemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="959557BABD50FF9E9B18FF7FDAC1DB2B" box="[1360,1436,250,271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFE92DAC1DB6D" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFE92DAC1DB6D" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">-. Mesopleuron densely rugose, rugose-reticulate or rugose-striate; scutellum slightly concave to flat; scape and pedicel, mandible, palpi yellowish brown; at least trochantellus of hind leg yellowish brown......................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD50FF9E9EDFFED7DAC1DBDD" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFED7DAC1DB85" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFED7DAC1DB85" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
2. Malar space 0.4× basal width of mandible; hind femur 7.0× longer than width; thyridium separated from basal margin of tergite by ca 3.0× its length; metasoma predominantly ferruginous; hind femur rusty reddish, dark brown ventrally............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9AE9FE09DAC1DB85" authority="Vas, 2020" authorityName="Vas" authorityYear="2020" box="[1185,1436,396,417]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeruginosus">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AE9FE09DAC1DB85" bold="true" box="[1185,1436,396,417]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AE9FE09DA6BDB85" bold="true" box="[1185,1334,396,417]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. aeruginosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D8434B22BD50FF9E9B74FE09DAC1DB85" author="Vas, Z." box="[1340,1436,396,417]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" pagination="247 - 264" refId="ref10278" refString="Vas, Z. (2020) New species and records of Charops Holmgren, 1859 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Campopleginae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 66 (3), 247 - 264. https: // doi. org / 10.17109 / AZH. 66.3.247.2020" type="journal article" year="2020">Vas, 2020</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFE2FDAC1DBDD" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFE2FDAC1DBDD" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
-. Malar space usually more than 0.4× basal width of mandible; hind femur 6.0–6.5× longer than width; thyridium separated from basal margin of tergite by approximately its length (except 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9D12FE42DCA3DBF8" authorityName=": Townes, Townes &amp; Gupta" authorityYear="1961" box="[858,1022,455,476]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachypterum">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9D12FE42DCA3DBF8" box="[858,1022,455,476]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. brachypterum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
3.0× its length); metasoma predominantly yellowish brown; hind femur yellowish brown or entirely black................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD50FF9E9EDFFD87DAC1D811" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFD87DAC1D833" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" box="[151,1436,513,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFD87DAC1D833" box="[151,1436,513,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">3. Propodeal medio-longitudinal carina distinct................................................................ 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFD9ADAC1D811" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" box="[151,1436,543,565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFD9ADAC1D811" box="[151,1436,543,565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">-. Propodeal medio-longitudinal carina obscure or absent....................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD50FF9E9EDFFDB9DAC1D88D" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFDB9DAC0D84B" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFDB9DAC0D84B" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
4. Mesopleuron rugose-striate; tegula pale yellow; fore and mid femora entirely yellow; hind tibia basally, first and second tarsal segments yellow.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9AD4FDDCDAC0D84B" authority="(Uchida, 1932)" baseAuthorityName="Uchida" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[1180,1437,601,623]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD4FDDCDAC0D84B" bold="true" box="[1180,1437,601,623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD4FDDCDA5CD84A" bold="true" box="[1180,1281,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. striatus</emphasis>
(Uchida, 1932)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFDF2DAC1D88D" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFDF2DAC1D88D" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
-. Mesopleuron rugose-reticulate; tegula black; fore femur with a black mark below; mid femur blackish brown except apically; hind tibia, first and second tarsal segments black........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9AD3FD11DAC1D88D" authority="Uchida, 1932" authorityName="Uchida" authorityYear="1932" box="[1179,1436,660,682]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD3FD11DAC1D88D" bold="true" box="[1179,1436,660,682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AD3FD11DA4DD88D" bold="true" box="[1179,1296,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. taiwanus</emphasis>
Uchida, 1932
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD50FF9E9EDFFD34DAC0D93B" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFD34DAC0D8C0" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD50FF9E9EDFFD34DAC0D8C0" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
5. Propodeal medio-longitudinal carina faintly indicated; hind femur and tibia yellowish brown; male genitalia short...................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD50FF9E9AC4FD4ADAC0D8C0" authority="(Szepligeti, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Szepligeti" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1164,1437,718,740]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Charops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AC4FD4ADAC0D8C0" bold="true" box="[1164,1437,718,740]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD50FF9E9AC4FD4ADBB0D8C0" bold="true" box="[1164,1261,718,740]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">C. bicolor</emphasis>
(Szépligeti,1906)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD50FF9E9EDFFD68DAC0D93B" blockId="5.[151,1437,220,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">
